The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for speaker change detection in dialog transcripts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SD (Sound) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of attention mechanisms, which could place it in cs.LG (Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
